Class SelectCarouselView

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node

pkgView.CarouselView
pkgView.SelectCarouselView
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class SelectCarouselView
extends CarouselView
Author:
Zane Greenholt The SelectCarouselView class extends CarouselView and holds the carousel implementation for the select plants screen. The images in this carousel can be clicked to be added to a collection of selected plants that will be remembered for the edit garden screen.

      public void filter​(java.lang.String sun, java.lang.String moisture, java.util.List<java.lang.String> soils)

      Parameters:
      sun - The sun level selected by the user on the draw garden screen
      moisture - The moisture level selected by the user on the draw garden screen
      soils - The soil type selected by the user on the draw garden screen

    • filter

      public void filter​(java.lang.String type, java.lang.String soil, java.lang.String sun, java.lang.String moisture, java.util.List<java.lang.String> soils)
      method that prepares the user chosen values to be Strings that can be used for filtering, and calls the filterCarousel method
      Parameters:
      type - Plant type selected by the user (woody or herbaceous)
      soil - Specific soil type selected by the user
      sun - Sun level selected by the user
      moisture - Moisture level selected by the user
      soils - List of all soil types used by the user to draw the garden
